Welcome to the CANS-F Assess and Plan for Change Application

Mark Lardner, Chapin Hall at the University of Chicago (mlardner@chapinhall.org)

Part # 1 - Entering Your Assessment

Step 1

For each new client, open the application by clicking the on the CANS-F Assess and Plan for Change file on your desktop (or wherever you have saved it).

*On some computers the "Enable Content" button will appear at the top of the screen after opening the file. This is a security feature for files that include macros. There are absolutely no security risks associated with using this application. Click "Enable Content" to continue.

Step 2

After opening the file, several worksheets are available at the bottom of the screen. Start by entering information into the Face Sheet.

Step 3

The Face Sheet has a series of drop downs and open text fields. Using the drop downs, you can select your Service Type, Office and the number of caregivers and youth to be assessed.

Step 4

After completing the Face Sheet (and selecting the number of caregivers and youth included in your assessment), click the "Assess" button towards the bottom of the page. You will notice additional worksheets have opened at the bottom of the screen. You should see a worksheet for each youth and caregiver in addition to the two family worksheets (Family Functioning and Caregiver Advocacy) that were already open.

Step 5

You are now ready to enter the assessment information. For each worksheet you need to:

  • identify the rating for each item,
  • offer a brief description where needed, and
  • identify strengths you will use in your plan and strengths that you plan to build with the youth and family.

Ratings can be entered using the drop down box or by typing into the field.

Not all strengths are available for rating. (Ex. Family Conflict, a family that manages conflict well might have a strength in Family Communication or Parental/Caregiver Collaboration, not Family Conflict). Only identify the strengths you plan to use or build by selecting yes from the drop down, the others strength fields can remain blank.

Step 6

For caregiver worksheets, enter the caregivers name before entering the caregiver ratings.

Step 7

For youth work sheets, enter the youths name, age and ID# before entering the youth ratings.

Step 8

When you have completed all the assessment worksheets, you are ready to begin planning with the youth and family. To assist with the planning process you can print the summary report by clicking on the "CANS-F Summary Sheet" button on the Face Sheet. The Summary Report includes all of the needs identified as actionable, the strengths identified as useful, the strengths you plan to build, and narrative about the familys goals and strengths.

Step 9

After navigating to the Summary Report worksheet:

  • click the "Adjust Rows" button to resize the rows to fit the text, and
  • click the "Print Summary Sheet" button.

The report will automatically print to your default printer. (You will need to be connected to a printer for this feature to work.)

Step 10

Save your completed assessment by clicking the "Save File" button on the Face Sheet. Identify the folder and name the file.

Congratulations!!! You have completed entering the assessment! You are ready for Part #2 - Completing the Plan for Change.
